host_about: I'm a professor at one of the local universities and a long-time Cambridge resident.  I live on the second floor at 64 Granville Road with my daughter. Whatever the season, we look forward to welcoming you when you're in Cambridge.

neighborhood_overview:

Somerville crossroads lives up to its hip image

“We’ve come from a foreign land called suburbia,” a mother joked to her two highly energized toddlers as they darted about on the busy sidewalks of Davis Square. On a sunny Saturday afternoon, urban bohemians and families alike swarmed into this hipster beehive to purge their cabin fever.

name: Bed and breakfast in Cambridge · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
host_about:
I have lived in my house in Cambridge for more than forty years, during which I have shared the space with family and first-floor tenants. I know well the advantages of this location, and I always enjoy connecting people with historic and cultural resources. In keeping with these enthusiasms, I volunteer as a guide at deCordova Sculpture Park and Museum in Lincoln and participate in projects at a community art center near my house.  I post about art in the Boston area on a blog called ART OUTDOORS. 
 (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

Currently a freelance writer and editor of educational materials, I keep a home office but still have one guest room that is not used often enough.  I think the room would prove to be a comfortable base for someone attending a conference or exploring the Boston area. 
I am vaccinated and boosted and try to follow whatever masking, testing, and cleaning guidelines are current.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.84 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Despite our urban setting, our neighborhood is very quiet, particularly at bedtime. It has always been the kind of neighborhood where women can walk alone safely at night. Generally speaking, this side of the river is dramatically calmer than the Boston side though now bustling with a nice variety of great restaurants.

We actively recycle. There is a blue bin in the unit. Or, we can do it for you if you simply keep glass, plastic and metal trash together and separated from trash. We also keep a compost container in the fridge for vegetable trash. We'll empty it into the big bin outside when you leave.
host_about:
We are a pair of classical musicians in Cambridge, located between MIT & Harvard. As with much of Cambridge, we're hopeless lefties. 

On parle un peu de français. Hablamos poco español. Und ein bisschen Deutsch auch.

Most Sundays you'll find us "making a joyful noise" at one church or another.
We've been in this old house and this neighborhood over 20 years now. Since we cook a bit, the rental floor fridge and pantry might contain a little overflow from ours. We're huge fans of Airbnb both as guests and as hosts. Leave your towels and sheets at home; we provide all that for you. Our biggest challenge as Airbnb hosts is saying goodbye to the awesome people who stay with us.

name: Bed and breakfast in Cambridge · ★4.92 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION!

If you are going to visit Boston and Cambridge, this is the place to stay. I am located in East Cambridge - near Kendall Square, MIT, Harvard, Massachusetts General Hospital, and Boston - with easy access to everything Boston and Cambridge have to offer. The Museum of Science, the Galeria Mall, and the Charles River are a short 3-5 block walk and there are plenty of shops and restaurants nearby.
host_about:
I have been hosting with Airbnb in my home since 2013 and am delighted to be back in business after our year of a COVID hiatus. Having received my second COVID vaccine, I am beginning to see a light at the end of this tunnel. I hope you are doing well and ready to travel again. New England is a great place to visit so I look forward to meeting you soon!

A little bit about me…
Originally from Florida, I found my way to New England via Spain where I lived and worked for 10 years! I have resided in Cambridge for the past 16 years and love everything it has to offer. I know the city well and can give you tips on things to do, places to see, and where to eat! 

My partner, Steve, and I are both retired from the education field. I was a Spanish teacher and he retired as a library director. We love to travel, cook, and spend time with friends and family.  

Hope you will plan to visit, we would love to host you.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.81 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is residential yet quite vibrant and has many services within walking distance. Two blocks in one direction is the wonderful café Sofra with homemade confections and middle eastern dishes. One block in the other direction is Shangri-La: an excellent Chinese restaurant. Two blocks away is Greg's, a neighborhood Italian eatery with full bar and early bird specials. Also within a block are a well stocked liquor store/wine shop, a middle eastern bakery, and a dry cleaners. If you want to walk five blocks to Coolidge Square there is a tasty vegetarian restaurant (Red Lentil), a great diner (Town Diner), a tiny but very good middle eastern eatery (Jasmine), and a super coffee/lunch spot (Uncommon Grounds). A supermarket (Shaws) is four blocks away. A jogging trail around Fresh Pond is six blocks away as is a very nice nine hole golf course. All of this only a ten minute bus ride from Harvard Square!
host_about: I am a long time Cambridge resident having come here originally to attend Harvard Divinity School. I'm a residential real estate agent practicing in Cambridge and Boston. I co-own a three-family residence in Fresh Pond Cambridge and rent out two rooms and a studio through airbnb at my residence where I also reside. I'm interested in health and help run a small meditation and holistic health group out of the first floor apartment in addition to the room rentals. My interests also include gardening, interior design, travel golf, and of course hosting on airbnb! I like providing beautiful and comfortable spaces for my guests to enjoy. I own an RV and love to go camping to the mountains and seashore with my friends and especially my grandchildren. My favorite travel destinations are New Orleans, Savannah, Georgia, and Palm Springs California. I like all kinds of foods and especially my veggies, and I'll give you my cole slaw recipe; grate a cabbage and some carrots, add a grated fresh anise and an apple to the mix, then add some organic cider vinegar and olive oil mayo to taste (this mix tastes so good, you can try it without mayo). My musical tastes are also wide and include jazz, pop, and a cappela.

name: Serviced apartment in Cambridge · ★4.65 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Live in the most exciting and vibrant neighborhood of Massachusetts. Kendall Square is a brimming area with cutting edge technology, science, design, innovation, creative restaurants, and fist-class shopping and is only a couple of metro stations away from downtown Boston. Take a few steps down the street and wander around the renowned Massachusetts Institute of Technology campus. Continue the knowledge tour at the Harvard University campus, where you’ll find peace and relax in its beautiful gardens and historic buildings. Unwind at the Charles River banks and enjoy the fantastic Boston views, where many trails and bike paths offer a haven to enjoy nature and a healthy lifestyle. Just across the Charles River you will be in downtown Boston surrounded by its gorgeous Revolution-era architecture and historic landmarks. The apartment is located in a modern high-rise boasting spectacular views and world-class resident amenities including a fitness center, a Zen garden, a clubhouse, and ful
host_about:
We have been providing vacation rental apartments for over 10 years across the East Coast. We are known for our distinctively furnished apartments in popular locations, and for our attentive service. You’ll find that our rates are quite reasonable. If you're looking for a safe, comfortable place with fabulous amenities and Wi-Fi (we know you need the Wi-Fi!) in the Boston MA area, Washington DC, Miami FL or very close to NYC in Jersey City or Hoboken, we'd love to host you. Many of the buildings where our apartments are located feature amenities such as beautiful lobbies, 24 hour front desk staff, fitness centers, business centers, recreation rooms, indoor or outdoor pools and whirlpools. If you are traveling with children, some buildings offer playgrounds (many buildings are near public playgrounds as well) or indoor playrooms. Depending on the location, you can stay for just a few days, a week, a month or more. 

We offer an assortment of short-term apartments in sizes ranging from a studio to three bedrooms that are fully furnished with all the comforts of home. Our local staff meticulously prepares your apartment before your arrival, and we offer 24 hour assistance for any emergencies after business hours. When you arrive at your apartment, the beds will be made, towels and bath amenities will be stocked in the bathrooms, and the coffee maker will be set up in the kitchen with some sample coffees, sweetener and creamer (teabags too if that is your preference) to start your morning off properly. If you’d like to cook a meal, the kitchen is stocked with dishes, cutlery, glassware and pots and pans. The living room is set up with a TV and cable channels, and the Wi-Fi router password and instructions will be prominently displayed so you can get connected quickly. You can also make local and toll-free phone calls at no charge. 

Please contact us to confirm the exact availability of the apartment you are interested in. We’d love to host you (and your family) for your vacation or business trip.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.92 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
In Central Square, easy access to lots of restaurants and bars. walking distance to Inman Square, Kendall Sq, Harvard Sq. Minutes to downtown on the subway. Easy access to zip cars and hubway bicycle service. There are three grocery stores within 5 minutes, Whole Foods, H-Mart and Harvest Coop.

There are a few drinking places; the Fields, Phoenix Landing, the Druid (Inman Sq) and Plough and Stars. They all serve food.

Restaurants are also abundant. It has a concentration of ethnic restaurants. For Indian, Central Square has Shalimar, India Pavilion and many others. There is Central Kitchen, Viale, Oleana, Ole, Casa Portugal, Dumpling House (Chinese) and Four Burgers. Flour is a short walk toward MIT and is known for its baked good and breakfast.
host_about: Architect who dabbles in making things.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.74 · 4 bedrooms · 5 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled up to Harvard and surrounds the neighborhood is quiet, well established, and beautiful with a lot of history and many famous residents past and current.

Located in the neighborhood of Cambridge called Huron Village, the home is blocks away from the historic Longfellow house, Harvard, Radcliff, Leslie and the entire area exudes Victorian charm.

There is easy and quick access to local stores, tree lines streets, and it offers exceptionally easy access to all things Cambridge and Boston, no car required!
host_about:
I love anything with a story behind it.  I really enjoy any sort of cultural event and great conversation.

In Phoenix, we have tried to provide the perfect sanctuary to get away and yet still see everything the city has to offer for events, shopping, dining, and natural beauty.  North Scottsdale near Kierland is absolutely the perfect location to be.

In Cambridge/Boston we are working with a 124-year-old Victorian.    It's beautiful with a lot of New England charm.   Many homes of the type in the area are gut remodeled and turned into condos or modern style living spaces.  We are working hard to maintain its hand-built Victorian charm while greening its infrastructure where possible and protecting it for future generations.   It's literally an antique we feel more like stewards than owners of.

We are now sharing these homes with others and using any money we earn to further the renovation projects.   We hope to meet people that will continue with us on this journey and get to enjoy things each time they come back as we further improve the spaces for all to enjoy.

name: Condo in Cambridge · ★4.58 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Enjoy all that Cambridge can offer (just about anything you can think of) without worrying about how to get there or having to carry anything with you: you can always stop by home for a few minutes of relaxation, have a meal delivered to you, check the internet, use your own facilities.... and then hop back into the swing of New England living. host_about: Lived in Cambridge for more than 15 years. Love the neighborhood.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.70 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:

Enjoy great coffee shops, top-rated restaurants and bars, and explore the city's vibrant cultural scene.

Other nearby attractions include the magnificent Cambridge Public Library and its beautiful park, just half a block away. For your convenience, a full grocery store and drug stores are only a 3-minute walk away.

Getting around is a breeze, with all major bus stops and the Harvard Square Red Line just minutes away. Whether you're here to be part of the Harvard community or heading to Boston, this unbeatable location puts it all within reach.

host_about: I am both Airbnb guest and host. From Toronto, Canada but resident of Cambridge, Massachusetts from 2008! I am a Harvard Alumni; I travel often to all corners of the world. and post COVID, I work from home remotely. I have a German Shepard dog that follows me everywhere I go.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is residential with a mixture of families with children, Harvard students and  professional people.   Our streets are not busy except in the morning and early evening hours when there is more street traffic. There are a few restaurants and a grocery store on nearby Huron Avenue, 2 blocks away. Many more restaurants and pubs can be found on Massachusetts Avenue and in Harvard, Central, Porter and Davis Squares .   During the day, the pleasantries of hearing children when they come out for recess from the two schools a block away is a happy sound, for me anyway.  Harvard University is  on the perimeter of our neighborhood.  M.I.T and other universities are easily reached by public transportation.
host_about:
I grew up in the Boston area, but lived some time in Europe and many years in Argentina and still have family and friends in Argentina.  

Interests cover much from enjoyment of nature, environmental concerns, sports and many cultural venues.  Work entails landscape design and maintenance focusing on ecology as well human impacts on land. 

Painting mainly on fine porcelain, writing and photography, music and theatre satisfy artistic desires.   I prefer to travel to places to live as a temporary resident to learn about other people, places and customs.

I also enjoy interacting with people of different backgrounds and countries around the world.  It is one of the most satisfying learning experience.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.93 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.85 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Cambridgeport is a quiet, residential neighborhood with a lot of history. There are 5 parks within a 10 minute walk. Central Square is our closest square - a 10 minute walk north. The Charles River and BU Bridge are a 10 minute walk south.
host_about: We have lived in Cambridge MA for over 30 years. We love the New England area and embrace all four seasons as well as the food and activities that come with them. In addition to loving this area, we both like to travel as much as we can. After all the years in Cambridge, we still love to discover new restaurants and activities in the Boston area and are looking forward to sharing those places with you when you come to visit. Our apartment is close to farmers' markets, interesting bars and restaurants, and public transportation to go anywhere in Boston or Cambridge. We are a 10 minute walk to the Charles River and its hike and bike paths as well as several Hubway bike rental spots. We'll happily loan you helmets! You can walk to Harvard, MIT and BU from our central location and even downtown Boston is only a little over a 1/2 hour walk. There's so much to see and do in this historic and interesting neighborhood. Come visit!

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.78 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

We look forward to meeting you and hope you enjoy your stay in Cambridge.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

Hello!

We have traveled the world together, attended & spoken at Airbnb’s international conferences, and hosted over 1000 guests. 

We created the honeymoon couples free stay program and are thrilled to continue offering our home through Airbnb’s valentines campaign.  

Bryan manages a bar & restaurant having started a pop up speak easy pre Covid & Marisa owns a small business.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.89 · 5 bedrooms · 5 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a quieter section of Cambridge.  Fresh Pond Reservation across the street has a 2 mile path for walking or jogging and many wooded areas to explore.  There are several great playgrounds within a short walk, and an assortment of small shops less than half a mile away in Huron Village, including a toy store, a grocery store, and a couple restaurants.  We live 1.5 miles from Harvard Square.  It is a very nice walk there, a 10 minute bus trip, or a $6-8 Uber ride.  Note that we do live on a busy road and traffic noise can be heard inside the house.  When windows are closed, it is barely noticeable.
host_about: We love to travel internationally with our four children and make our home available to other travelers while we are away.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.84 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This is an old neighborhood of owner occupied homes once used as servants' quarters for the Brattle Street mansions near Harvard Square in the old, Victorian days. We neighbors all know each other, so things run smoothly. It is safe, quiet, friendly, and has GREAT coffee steps away.
host_about: Artist, textile/accessories designer, and global traveler with a particular love for Asian markets, vintage textiles, and artisans !! My daughter and I lived in Vietnam for the better part of 7 years, and our home is definitely a mini gallery of our travels. I am positive you will feel very happy to be in the midst of lovely colors, interesting books, and, best of all, in a seemingly quiet corner of Cambridge, tucked away, that in actuality — is in the center of all!

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Strawberry Hill is a very friendly neighborhood between Huron Ave and Mount Auburn Street. There are numerous little places by local owners offering a multitude of food within a ten minute walk.  All along Belmont Street one can find - Sofra ( a spinoff from Oleana) is a quick walk away; Eastern Lemejun has delicous Armenian & middle eastern offerings; Conleys Pub and sports bar is always serving up food and drinks; Homemade Greek yogurts and foods can be found at Sophia's on Belmont St, and just before that Linda's Donuts makes the best home made donuts from scratch every morning; Fiorellas has pizza and Italian; At Aram's Cafe, one can get a breakfast or lunch cooked by Aram himself, whose establishment has been cooking up delicious entrees for over 30 years; Moozies Ice cream for homemade ice cream and an outdoor movie screen in warm weather. There is a large supermarket, liquor store and drug store in Star Market as well as local food shops. The Fresh Pond Golf Course and Waterwork
host_about: I am an artist, cook, gardener, mom and teacher. I love to bike around FreshPond, kayak on the Charles River, watch my children's sports games, head to Rhode Island (my hometown ) for the beach. I love the city and all it has to offer.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Here are a few of my favorite things about my location:
1) Restaurants/Cafes/Bars less than 0.25 miles away include: Sofra, Red Lentil, Greg's, Cha Yen Thai Cookery, Deluxe Town Diner, Seta's Cafe, The Village Kitchen.
2) I love walking around and enjoying the beautiful homes, gardens and parks in the neighborhood.
3) Proximity to Harvard Square - you really can't beat it. You can be at the heart of Harvard Square in less than 5 minutes by bus or car.
4) Great live music - There are a number of live music venues nearby.
5) The Cambridge Public Library and newly renovated Harvard Art Museums are beautiful spaces with great architectural design and are within a walking distance from my place and they both are great places to spend the day.
6) Fresh Pond and Mt. Auburn Cemetery, two highlights, are within a 10 min walk.
host_about:
I'm a Designer/Education Entrepreneur. My company is based in Boston, but I'm a native Californian. I grew up in Southern California and got transplanted to the chilly East Coast. Let's just say, I'm still getting used to the winters!

I've been living in Cambridge for the past 6 years, and have come to enjoy the intellectual environment and diversity of the city.

I love art, electronic music, traveling, trying new restaurants, watching indie movies, and working on interactive art projects in my spare time.

I love to make guests feel welcome and comfortable and to share the joys of Cambridge living.

name: Condo in Cambridge · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Easy walking distance to both Kendall and Inman squares. Close to lots shops, restaurants, and public transport (green line Lechmere and red line Kendall Square stops). 5 min walk to a large grocery store (Star Market).

Inman Sq and East Cambridge are vibrant, multicultural communities. You're only steps away from delicious Portuguese and Italian restaurants, Atwood's Tavern (great burgers with live music on the patio), Lone Star Taco Bar (fresh take on Mexican), Puritan & Company (modern New England), and Christina's (a classic Cambridge ice cream parlor)

name: Guest suite in Cambridge · ★4.91 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: West Cambridge is a hot neighborhood at the moment, with great urban amenities and excellent green spaces. Nestled between the historic homes of Brattle St, the unique shops of Huron Village and the green spaces of Fresh Pond reservoir and Danehy Park, there's lots to do and see. Jog or walk the 2 mile loop around the Pond, explore historic neighborhoods and sample the many interesting food shops. Or wander down to Harvard Square and all the university has to offer with museums and bookstores galore. Major retailers like Whole Foods and Starbucks are also a short walk away.
host_about:
I have lived in Cambridge for over 25 years.  I moved here for graduate school at Harvard and never left.  Currently, I'm a baker and  pastry chef  ( Instagram:  @hazelnama ) working part time in local bakeries.   However, my primary job is raising our eleven year old son.

I love to travel and have been all over world (most of that before having a child).  My partner and I spend a good deal of time in Maine but are plotting trips much further out as our son gets a little older.  

As a host I'm very accessible but mostly hands off.  I'm more than happy to answer any questions, point you in the direction of great restaurants or sights but tend to let our guests enjoy the space as they like.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.43 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This is an excellent location, featuring a beautiful house in a wonderful neighbohood, nearby Central Square and Inman square, with the Red Line Subway, Bus routes,  excellent restaurants, Whole Foods, and much more in short walking distance.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.86 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Wonderful walking neighborhood. Harvard sq, park and reservoir all easy walk. Many great cafes, restaurants and shops close by. Foodies will appreciate nearby Huron village.
host_about: Brian and I have lived in Cambridge for many years. We welcome you to our house and the best neighborhood in town. The apt is on the first floor, we live upstairs on the third fl. We travel, but if away will always make sure you have whatever you need.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.71 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled up to Harvard and surrounds the neighborhood is quiet, well established, and beautiful with a lot of history and many famous residents past and current.

Located in the neighborhood of Cambridge called Huron Village, the home is blocks away from the historic Longfellow house, Harvard, MIT, Radcliffe, Leslie and the entire area exudes Victorian charm.

There is easy and quick access to local stores, tree lines streets, and it offers exceptionally easy access to all things Cambridge and Boston, no car required!
host_about:
I love anything with a story behind it.  I really enjoy any sort of cultural event and great conversation.

In Phoenix, we have tried to provide the perfect sanctuary to get away and yet still see everything the city has to offer for events, shopping, dining, and natural beauty.  North Scottsdale near Kierland is absolutely the perfect location to be.

In Cambridge/Boston we are working with a 124-year-old Victorian.    It's beautiful with a lot of New England charm.   Many homes of the type in the area are gut remodeled and turned into condos or modern style living spaces.  We are working hard to maintain its hand-built Victorian charm while greening its infrastructure where possible and protecting it for future generations.   It's literally an antique we feel more like stewards than owners of.

We are now sharing these homes with others and using any money we earn to further the renovation projects.   We hope to meet people that will continue with us on this journey and get to enjoy things each time they come back as we further improve the spaces for all to enjoy.

host_about: This Cambridge local has been living in their charming home for over 20 years and knows the ins and outs of the city. With 6 years of hosting experience under their belt, you can trust that they will make your stay comfortable and unforgettable. From insider tips on the best local restaurants to providing a cozy and inviting atmosphere in their home, this host goes above and beyond for their guests. Experience true Cambridge hospitality!

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
North Cambridge ( NoCa) is a wonderful quiet neighborhood, and Hollis is one of the nicest streets in NoCa! It is a one way street, and traffic on the street is pretty light. Massachusetts ave is just abut 100 yards up, and within a 5 minute walk you will find many fine restaurants ( two sushi, one Greek, one Italian, one Vietnamese- French, one steak house, one Chinese), a produce market, a dry cleaner, and three banks. There is a CVS in Porter square, about a 10 minute walk on Mass Avenue, and the MINUTE CLINIC there is open 8am- 7 pm.
Additionally, at the end of Rindge Avenue end of Hollis, you will find branch of the Cambridge Public Library, and great play ground with both toddler and "big kid" sections, ball fields, and tennis courts.
And if you are looking for more night life, Davis Square, with a huge variety of restaurants, bars, gift shops, and hipsters, is about a 7 minute walk.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.63 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath

There is a binder in the apartment with information on great places to see and interesting things to do.
host_about: Academic prof at one of the colleges in Cambridge has an extra condo dedicated to airbnb guests. My girlfriend, who is German and myself love to travel all over the world to experience different peoples and cultures. We live in Cambridge not far from the units and absolutely love the neighborhood. We would love to host you in this very cosy space, tastely decorated and furnished condo that used to call our primary home.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.82 · 5 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: In our Cambridgeport neighborhood, you can walk to restaurants, cafes, and shops in Central and Harvard Squares, grocery stores (Whole Foods and Trader Joes), and the Charles River. host_about: I am a Middle Grade/Young Adult writer (High) and editor, and I teach at Harvard Summer School and Harvard Extension School. name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.99 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood is very special in that it is quiet, you can hear birdsong most times of the day, there are lovely gardens all around. And you will be just 3 blocks from Massachusetts Avenue (Mass Ave), the busiest street in Boston/Cambridge. Or, if you are here in winter, the quiet of the cold air is lovely too, and if we are lucky, you'll see snow!

Along Mass Ave, you can walk to many local run businesses of every sort: gift shops (Joie de Vivre, Nomad, Abodeon, Tokai), coffee shops (Simons, Hi-Rise, Starbucks) and so many restaurants of every ethnicity (Indian, Japanese, Thai, Italian, Mexican, American). You can take a walk from here to the Charles River, through Harvard Square. You can stroll down Mass Ave to Central Square where there is a whole new world waiting for you, but just as Cambridge as any other place! Somerville is just minutes away too (Davis Square, Inman Square, Union Square), and it is an amazingly rich community for music, food and funky shops
host_about:

neighborhood_overview:
The condo is nestled in a safe and friendly neighborhood in the heart of Cambridge, MA. This prime and well-connected location, with a Walk Score of 98, offers everything you need within walking distance.

One of the main draws of Cambridge is its world-renowned universities, including Harvard University and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). Take a guided tour of these campuses to learn about their history, see their beautiful architecture, or explore independently.

Beyond the universities, Cambridge has several excellent museums and cultural institutions. For example, the Harvard Museum of Natural History features exhibits on everything from dinosaurs to gemstones, while the MIT Museum showcases the latest advances in science and technology. The Harvard Art Museums are a must-visit for art lovers, with collections ranging from ancient Greek pottery to contemporary paintings.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.85 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: A stone's throw away, yet hidden from the bustle of Fresh Pond Parkway, this apartment is within walking distance of shops and restaurants, including Trader Joe's, Whole Foods, Chipotle, TJ Maxx, and a movie theater. Equally accessible to two of Cambridge's largest green spaces -- Fresh Pond Reservoir and Danehy Park. Close to public transportation (subway & bus) to take you anywhere around Cambridge and Boston. For the adventurous, ride along the Minuteman Bikeway from Alewife out to historic Lexington and Bedford.
host_about:
Travelling is a passion of mine.   I love to experience new places, new foods and meet new people.   Having lived in Brazil, Japan, Thailand and many years here in the United States I appreciate diverse viewpoints and customs.    Getting helpful insight from friendly locals makes any stay so much richer.

For my day job, I develop multifamily housing.   I am interested in creating living solutions that allow residents to pursue their passions and interests while having a smaller environmental footprint.    To that end, I am involved in a startup that uses architectural robotics to create transformable spaces.

As a father of five, I am a family man.   I appreciate the challenges and joys of travelling with family.    My wife and I took our children down the Silk Road on a 3 week hand carry only trip.   Getting good local advice can be critical to making a stay pleasant and rewarding for every member of the family.

neighborhood_overview:
My place is in North Cambridge and more residential. It's along the border with Somerville and close to Arlington. Century(s) old classic "Double/Triple Deckers" are common and young or youngish professionals, students and young families live in the mostly renovated homes.

Though quiet, its location is very close free live music nightly in Davis or Porter squares, and probably over 50 restaurants within walking distance.
host_about:
I'm new to Airbnb and wondering why I haven't hosted at my place before.  My work is in health care both clinical and in research regulation.  For fun I bike, hike, climb, play soccer, and take excursions both near and far when the opportunity arises.   
Favorite places are Seattle where I lived years, and Central and South America where I work/volunteer when possible.  Nearby, Davis Square,sailing in Boston Harbor, or road trips in New England top the list.  
I've mainly been a solo traveler and have skipped across the world at a rapid pace from hostel to hostel, now I'm looking for more focused trips and Airbnb seems to be the best answer for this.  
I have my first guest currently, and I look forward to many more in the future, and from all over the world.  
My dog is extremely friendly, quiet and would love the company as well.  We will consider travelers with pets.  
Happy traveling!

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.92 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Mount Auburn Street is a tree lined street with an eclectic array of local gardens lining the sidewalk.  The neighborhood is part of the Half Crown Marsh Conservation District with mostly Victorian architecture    The house is four doors away from Longfellow Park - designed by Charles Elliot in 1887.  Across the street is Riverbend Park where you can sit on a bench and watch the Charles River where rowing teams from the various universities often practice.  We have two cafes in the neighborhood. Darwins and Flour both very good and both close. Memorial Drive which runs alongside the Charles River ( a short block from our house) is closed for biking, roller skating etc. from 11am to 7pm on Sundays from the last Sunday in April until the 2nd Sunday in November.  Because of major universities located in Cambridge, the city is very international and you will hear many different languages spoken

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.84 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
It's quiet, charming, and only 5 minutes from the train! My neighborhood is a safe oasis of fabulous food and cute shops.

Harvard is a 15 minute walk. There you can enjoy Harvard Square, tour Harvard campus, explore historical points of interest, visit Harvard's art museums, see American historical sights, and enjoy coffee while people-watching.

Central Square is a 6 minute walk (there is a train stop there.) At Central, you'll find quirky dive bars, a cool used book store, juice bar, vegan/ vegetarian/farm-to-table restaurants, live music, record shops, thrift shops, yoga, and art galleries.

MIT is a 15 minute walk. You can take a guided tour and enjoy the MIT Museum, free interactive public art, and gardens.

A Hubway bike station is a 5 minute walk.

Inman Square is a 2 minute walk. There you'll find:
City Girl Cafe- phenomenal brunch & dinners in eclectic tiny restaurant
Punjabi Dhaba- award-winning Indian "street food
host_about:
Gleeful epicurean and traveler, always planning or returning from a trip.

Polyglot—I studied Swahili, Portuguese, Spanish, French, and Latin. I explore street markets until they close or kick me out. Can't live without passport, antique books, botany, kids & dogs, dinner club, gelato...

I mentor startups at Harvard and work in finance. 

Hosting is a blast; I give guests privacy, but I'm always available to help or make recommendations. I treat guests like fam and surprise them with treats. 

Everyone is welcome!

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 baths

Just a block or two away from the apartment are tons of restaurants and coffee shops, making it easy to try all of the delicious cuisine in the area! We are also located in between two Whole Foods, and just two blocks away from a Walgreens. We love living here because it's so easy to get around. name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.77 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The suite is located in North Cambridge, near the hip and vibrant Davis Square, Somerville, just a 5 min. walk away along Linear Park. Linear Park is a charming well lit pathway that is well trafficked day and night by folks day and night, walking back and forth to Davis Square, often with street music performers at points along the way.

Davis Square is certainly a cultural location, with shows and movies to see at the Somerville Theatre, in addition to Somerville Open Studios, ArtBeat, HONK! to name but a few of the many festivals the occur in the town around the year.

Davis Square is also a dining destination. There's something for everyone in these blocks, from barbecue to vegan fare. One can find the cuisines of Mexico, Italy, China, India, Japan, and more. And there are new places to find delicious food opening all the time.

And for nightlife, there are no shortage of bars, from the casual to the hip and trendy with fine beverages and food on offer

Serviced apartment in Cambridge · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Live in the most exciting and vibrant neighborhood of Massachusetts. Kendall Square is a brimming area with cutting edge technology, science, design, innovation, creative restaurants, and fist-class shopping and is only a couple of metro stations away from downtown Boston. Take a few steps down the street and wander around the renowned Massachusetts Institute of Technology campus. Continue the knowledge tour at the Harvard University campus, where you’ll find peace and relax in its beautiful gardens and historic buildings. Unwind at the Charles River banks and enjoy the fantastic Boston views, where many trails and bike paths offer a haven to enjoy nature and a healthy lifestyle. Just across the Charles River you will be in downtown Boston surrounded by its gorgeous Revolution-era architecture and historic landmarks. The apartment is located in a modern high-rise boasting spectacular views and world-class resident amenities including a fitness center, a Zen garden, a clubhouse, and ful
host_about:
We have been providing vacation rental apartments for over 10 years across the East Coast. We are known for our distinctively furnished apartments in popular locations, and for our attentive service. You’ll find that our rates are quite reasonable. If you're looking for a safe, comfortable place with fabulous amenities and Wi-Fi (we know you need the Wi-Fi!) in the Boston MA area, Washington DC, Miami FL or very close to NYC in Jersey City or Hoboken, we'd love to host you. Many of the buildings where our apartments are located feature amenities such as beautiful lobbies, 24 hour front desk staff, fitness centers, business centers, recreation rooms, indoor or outdoor pools and whirlpools. If you are traveling with children, some buildings offer playgrounds (many buildings are near public playgrounds as well) or indoor playrooms. Depending on the location, you can stay for just a few days, a week, a month or more. 

We offer an assortment of short-term apartments in sizes ranging from a studio to three bedrooms that are fully furnished with all the comforts of home. Our local staff meticulously prepares your apartment before your arrival, and we offer 24 hour assistance for any emergencies after business hours. When you arrive at your apartment, the beds will be made, towels and bath amenities will be stocked in the bathrooms, and the coffee maker will be set up in the kitchen with some sample coffees, sweetener and creamer (teabags too if that is your preference) to start your morning off properly. If you’d like to cook a meal, the kitchen is stocked with dishes, cutlery, glassware and pots and pans. The living room is set up with a TV and cable channels, and the Wi-Fi router password and instructions will be prominently displayed so you can get connected quickly. You can also make local and toll-free phone calls at no charge. 

Please contact us to confirm the exact availability of the apartment you are interested in. We’d love to host you (and your family) for your vacation or business trip.

name: Bed and breakfast in Cambridge · ★4.98 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview: If you are going to visit Cambridge or Boston, this is a great place to stay. Huron Village is a quiet neighborhood full of families, walkers, runners and bicyclists. Its safe to walk here both day and night.  You can stop for a great dinner in Harvard Square and then enjoy a leisurely walk back to Huron Village along historic Brattle street.
host_about: I am a retired science teacher and school administrator.  When I travel, I love to go on  walking holidays. Walking allows me to pay more attention to the landscape and the surrounding architecture, which I love the most.   My favorite walking holiday so far has been through Cornwall, England.  No matter where I go, I always try to seek out some good jazz - especially Latin jazz! The small local music venues are often the best.   I have always been  curious about people, who they are, where they are from and what are their life stories. I look forward to lots of interesting conversations as both a host and a guest.
property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
This is located at Harvard Square, a fantastic and historic area. There are dozens of great restaurants, shops, and history about 30 seconds from the door.

It's a cultural hub--you'll find tons of diverse food (Thai, Indian, Italian, Asian, Gastro, New American, Venezuelan!) and activities down the street. The Museum of Natural History is a 5 minute walk, and the renowned Harvard Art Museums are a 10 minute walk. Harvard Law School is literally 10 meters from the apartment.

The Red Line train is right in the center of Harvard Square. It's easy and inexpensive to take the train to any location in Boston or Cambridge.
host_about:
Gleeful epicurean and traveler, always planning or returning from a trip.

Polyglot—I studied Swahili, Portuguese, Spanish, French, and Latin. I explore street markets until they close or kick me out. Can't live without passport, antique books, botany, kids & dogs, dinner club, gelato...

I mentor startups at Harvard and work in finance. 

Hosting is a blast; I give guests privacy, but I'm always available to help or make recommendations. I treat guests like fam and surprise them with treats. 

Everyone is welcome!

neighborhood_overview:
One of the best neighborhoods in Cambridge! We're close to everything. The subway is right up the street. Historic Harvard Square is a 10-15 min walk with the University, historic sites, great food, shopping, and bustling street life.
We're just half a block away from Mass Ave, which stretches between Harvard and Porter Square and is lined with cute shops, cafes, restaurants, etc. Check out our Guidebook!

host_about:
Hi!

We are a married couple living in a big beautiful house in Cambridge. Jarrod is a scientist and Rae is a painter. We're pretty low key- when we're not working hard, we like to relax at home, explore local history, or check out antique shops.

We're friendly and are happy to be helpful in any way possible, but mostly keep to ourselves. Since our rooms to rent are separated from our living space, we might not encounter our guests at all, but are always available to answer questions.

Walk 10 minutes to MIT or 20 minutes to Harvard or take the T and be in either Harvard Square or Boston in 2 minutes.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated on Kendall Square at the intersection of Main Street and Broadway. The area hosts MIT and a variety of co-working spaces and incubators, ideal for bright young minds. It is home to a cutting-edge tech community and has thus become one of the world's most important tech and biotech centers. Farm-to-table restaurants and third-wave coffee joints have also found their places around this startup culture. The Cambridge neighborhood, which is a top destination for shopping, is centered around Kendall Square. The Kendall transit stop is only a 4-minute walk away via Main Street.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: Condo in Cambridge · ★4.91 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Walk friendly: Walking distance (12-20 mins) to MIT, Kendall square, and east and mid Cambridge. A longer walk (~1.4 mi) or short Uber/Lyft ride to Harvard.

Runner friendly: Warm up with a walk/run ~1 mile to get to the Charles river, and then run a loop taking one bridge across the river to Boston and another back to create a 3 mile or 4 mile loop (depending on the bridge), and then cool down another ~1 mile to get back home. Except the bridges, Cambridge/Boston is really flat, perfect for easy jogs.

Groceries: Multiple Whole Foods locations within ~0.6 to ~0.8 miles; Star Market ~0.6 miles away; H Mart ~0.9 miles away.
host_about: Scientist, traveler, coffee lover, fitness freak, host, and an optimist with perhaps an irrational faith in humanity.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.92 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Historic, posh Avon Hill neighborhood is great for walking. This part of Cambridge in general has an abundance of old Victorian homes over several square miles. The Cooper-Frost-Austin house (1681), oldest in Cambridge, is just down the street. Raymond Park and playground is nearby as well. The Harvard campus is a short distance away, and in addition to the famous yard proposes the Natural History Museum and its renowned Art Museum. Historic Cambridge Common, where General Washington's troops assembled, is nearby as well. The Porter Square subway stop is a 3-minute walk, and one stop away from Davis square or Harvard Square.

For shopping an errands, we recommend:

Porter Square Post Office
Porter Square Book store
Caffe Nero
Cafe Bourbon
The Abbey (bistro)
Bagelsaurus bakery
The Toad (cozy live music bar)
Christopher's (bistro and sports bar)
Colette Wine Bar and Restaurant
Yume Wo Katare ramen bar
Lunder Arts Cen
host_about: Marie and Andrew have been living in Cambridge for a dozen years. Marie grew up in the romantic city of Paris, and is now a filmmaker and script writer. She also loves to cook and read. Andrew hails from the south, moved to Paris to study architecture, and now runs a design and visualization practice in Cambridge. Andrew and Marie love to travel and strike up unexpected friendships.

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.28 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 2 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood houses one of the best-known high-tech and innovation hubs of the United States and arguably has the highest concentration of PhD's in the world.

However, this neighborhood is probably the most "below the radar" for tourists, but what it lacks in glamour it more than makes up for it in total, earnest hidden-gem-ness. Cruise down its main aorta, Cambridge Street, for access to some of the best fish markets, Portuguese bakeries, and well-loved bars in town. Mall rats can get their fill between the Cambridgeside Galleria and the Twin City Plaza shopping center, but one would be remiss to pass up stylish treasures at the Cambridge Antique Market. The residential makeup is richly diverse, anchored with strong Irish and Portuguese communities. Local pride runs thick.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · ★4.95 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
This is located at Harvard Square, a fantastic historic area. There are dozens of great restaurants, shops, and history about 30 seconds from the door!

It's a cultural hub--you'll find tons of diverse food (Thai, Indian, Italian, Asian, Gastro, New American, Venezuelan!) and activities down the street.

The Museum of Natural History is a 5 minute walk, and the renowned Harvard Art Museums are a 10 minute walk. Harvard Law School is literally 10 meters from the apartment.

The Red Line train is right in the center of Harvard Square. It's easy and inexpensive to take the train to any location in Boston or Cambridge.
host_about:
Gleeful epicurean and traveler, always planning or returning from a trip.

Polyglot—I studied Swahili, Portuguese, Spanish, French, and Latin. I explore street markets until they close or kick me out. Can't live without passport, antique books, botany, kids & dogs, dinner club, gelato...

I mentor startups at Harvard and work in finance. 

Hosting is a blast; I give guests privacy, but I'm always available to help or make recommendations. I treat guests like fam and surprise them with treats. 

Everyone is welcome!

name: Home in Cambridge · ★4.98 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
We're in an amazing location and walking distance to many cafes, restaurants, breweries, a Formaggio cheese shop, and an indie theater (Kendall Square Cinema). One of Boston's best restaurants is right around the corner (Cafe du Pays) as is one of Boston's must try watering holes: Lamplighter Brewery, not to mention Lord Hobo and Mead Hall. Vincent’s is also nearby with tasty breakfast tacos. Flour Bakery + Cafe, one of the best spots in Boston, is a short 10 - 15 min walk.

MIT and Kendall Square are less than 10 minutes by foot. Have an interview? This is the place to stay. We're just a few steps from Pfizer, Akamai, Novartis, Fa*ebook, G**gle, Microsoft, Apple, Moderna, Broad Institute, Draper, Biogen, Sanofi, Takeda, CIC, MIT-Sloan, and so many more.

Harvard and downtown Boston are just a short two stops away on the T (Boston's subway), as are all of the tourist attractions.
host_about:
I'm an Architect and designer in Boston. Former San Franciscan and Seattelite.
My partner Luis is a planner and developer. He is a native East Coaster.

We love to travel and are in California frequently. We love to travel and look forward to meeting folks from all over the world.

If you travel anything like us, we think you'll be very happy and we look forward to being your host!

'The Square' (as it is sometimes referred to locally) is both a commercial and residential center. Bookstores, theatres and music venues line the streets and enhance the energetic atmosphere. The neighborhood's central location, close proximity to university campuses and many public transportation options make it a bustling hub for people of all ages. During the day, take a stroll and discover the area's tranquil scenery. At night, there are countless bar and entertainment options. On the T, Downtown is a 15 minute ride while Logan International Airport is 30 minutes away.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated on Kendall Square at the intersection of Main Street and Broadway. The area hosts MIT and a variety of co-working spaces and incubators, ideal for bright young minds. It is home to a cutting-edge tech community and has thus become one of the world's most important tech and biotech centers. Farm-to-table restaurants and third-wave coffee joints have also found their places around this startup culture. The Cambridge neighborhood, which is a top destination for shopping, is centered around Kendall Square. The Kendall transit stop is only a 4-minute walk away via Main Street.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Central Square, Cambridge, which is centered on the junction of Massachusetts Avenue, Prospect Street and Western Avenue. The diverse area is well known for its wide variety of ethnic restaurants, bars, live music and theatre venues. Many startups have moved research and office operations into the Square to take advantage of the relatively low costs and the proximity to MIT. Nearly demolished in the 1950’s, the neighborhood was spared and went so far as to experience a sort of renaissance. In 2012, the state of Massachusetts designated Central Square as an official Cultural District.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Cambridge, Massachusetts is a charming, diverse city adjacent to Boston with beautiful views of the Charles River. A college town home to Harvard University and MIT, Cambridge is on the cutting edge of education, research and development. Residents of Cambridge enjoy being in the Greater Boston area without the hustle and bustle of Boston proper, creating the perfect balance between urban living and a suburban feel. Students attending college and living in the area hail from all over the world, giving Cambridge a worldly, international flavor. Harvard Square boasts historic red brick walkways and tree-lined blocks full of restaurants, shops, museums, entertainment centers and bookstores. The nearby Central Square is teeming with eclectic restaurants, bars, live music venues and small theaters. . Cambridge is an easy commute from downtown Boston via the “T” and the bus. Kendall Square and Central Square are within walking distance of Boston, just over the Charles River.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Cambridge, Massachusetts is a charming, diverse city adjacent to Boston with beautiful views of the Charles River. A college town home to Harvard University and MIT, Cambridge is on the cutting edge of education, research and development. Residents of Cambridge enjoy being in the Greater Boston area without the hustle and bustle of Boston proper, creating the perfect balance between urban living and a suburban feel. Students attending college and living in the area hail from all over the world, giving Cambridge a worldly, international flavor. Harvard Square boasts historic red brick walkways and tree-lined blocks full of restaurants, shops, museums, entertainment centers and bookstores. The nearby Central Square is teeming with eclectic restaurants, bars, live music venues and small theaters. . Cambridge is an easy commute from downtown Boston via the “T” and the bus. Kendall Square and Central Square are within walking distance of Boston, just over the Charles River.

neighborhood_overview: Central Square is truly the center of everything that's happening in Cambridge. Located right in between Harvard Square and Kendall Square (MIT), it's walking distance to both institutions and all the research centers in the area. I used to bike from Harvard to MIT when I was a student, a very pleasant 15 minute ride. Harvard Street is just two streets north of Massachusetts Avenue, which is the main street that connects these school and also directly leads to downtown. A simple search shows that there're more than twenty 4-Star+ coffee shops and countless 4-Star+ restaurants, you can walk to restaurants, coffee shops, grocery stores, universities, just about everywhere.
host_about:
A world traveler trapped inside a body of an entrepreneur who wants to make the world a better place to live. This career path gave me the freedom to control my time and hence I was able to travel internationally at least a few times a year, I've been to over 15 countries across four continents, the pace's just too slow. I love staying at Airbnb to get local tips, make new friends, and as a way for me to enrich my global experience without physically traveling there, I want to become a host as well. Boston is a tourist destination for many reasons, and in Cambridge, I meet many intelligent, fun, and creative people all around the world. I hope to be a host and local guide for those who visiting Cambridge and Boston. 

My No.1 recommendation of a Must-watch movie: "Good Will Hunting". If you are coming to Boston/Cambridge, please do watch that movie, it will add some color to your Boston experience.

Red brick buildings, parks and public spaces, cultural attractions, and an invigorating pace of life give the feel of a buzzing European hotspot, where an eclectic mix of young tech professionals and the lively campus communities of Harvard and MIT spill over into the area’s many restaurants, cosy bars, and craft coffee shops. Sitting along the north bank of the Charles River just a few T stops away from downtown Boston, Cambridge’s leafy, sustainably-minded neighborhoods are bursting with things to see and do for every season.

neighborhood_overview: Central Square is truly the center of everything that's happening in Cambridge. Located right in between Harvard Square and Kendall Square (MIT), it's walking distance to both institutions and all the research centers in the area. I used to bike from Harvard to MIT when I was a student, a very pleasant 15 minute ride. Harvard Street is just two streets north of Massachusetts Avenue, which is the main street that connects these school and also directly leads to downtown. A simple search shows that there're more than twenty 4-Star+ coffee shops and countless 4-Star+ restaurants, you can walk to restaurants, coffee shops, grocery stores, universities, just about everywhere.
host_about:
A world traveler trapped inside a body of an entrepreneur who wants to make the world a better place to live. This career path gave me the freedom to control my time and hence I was able to travel internationally at least a few times a year, I've been to over 15 countries across four continents, the pace's just too slow. I love staying at Airbnb to get local tips, make new friends, and as a way for me to enrich my global experience without physically traveling there, I want to become a host as well. Boston is a tourist destination for many reasons, and in Cambridge, I meet many intelligent, fun, and creative people all around the world. I hope to be a host and local guide for those who visiting Cambridge and Boston. 

My No.1 recommendation of a Must-watch movie: "Good Will Hunting". If you are coming to Boston/Cambridge, please do watch that movie, it will add some color to your Boston experience.

neighborhood_overview: Cambridge, Massachusetts is a charming, diverse city adjacent to Boston with beautiful views of the Charles River. A college town home to Harvard University and MIT, Cambridge is on the cutting edge of education, research and development. Residents of Cambridge enjoy being in the Greater Boston area without the hustle and bustle of Boston proper, creating the perfect balance between urban living and a suburban feel. Students attending college and living in the area hail from all over the world, giving Cambridge a worldly, international flavor. Harvard Square boasts historic red brick walkways and tree-lined blocks full of restaurants, shops, museums, entertainment centers and bookstores. The nearby Central Square is teeming with eclectic restaurants, bars, live music venues and small theaters. . Cambridge is an easy commute from downtown Boston via the “T” and the bus. Kendall Square and Central Square are within walking distance of Boston, just over the Charles River.
host_about: Furnished Quarters has been helping people stay different for 25 years. Driven by a passion for providing reliable short-term housing solutions worldwide, we aim to empower our guests with a seamless experience. Our prime locations in sought-after destinations, 24/7 guest service, expert design, and hand-picked furnishings in every one of our high-quality homes come together to create a simplified but sophisticated stay, every time.

name: Boutique hotel in Cambridge · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 4 beds · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview: Central Square is truly the center of everything that's happening in Cambridge. Located right in between Harvard Square and Kendall Square (MIT), it's walking distance to both institutions and all the research centers in the area. I used to bike from Harvard to MIT when I was a student, a very pleasant 15 minute ride. Harvard Street is just two streets north of Massachusetts Avenue, which is the main street that connects these school and also directly leads to downtown. A simple search shows that there're more than twenty 4-Star+ coffee shops and countless 4-Star+ restaurants, you can walk to restaurants, coffee shops, grocery stores, universities, just about everywhere.
host_about:
A world traveler trapped inside a body of an entrepreneur who wants to make the world a better place to live. This career path gave me the freedom to control my time and hence I was able to travel internationally at least a few times a year, I've been to over 15 countries across four continents, the pace's just too slow. I love staying at Airbnb to get local tips, make new friends, and as a way for me to enrich my global experience without physically traveling there, I want to become a host as well. Boston is a tourist destination for many reasons, and in Cambridge, I meet many intelligent, fun, and creative people all around the world. I hope to be a host and local guide for those who visiting Cambridge and Boston. 

My No.1 recommendation of a Must-watch movie: "Good Will Hunting". If you are coming to Boston/Cambridge, please do watch that movie, it will add some color to your Boston experience.

host_about:
We are both designers and love what we do :-) Jordan owns a Design Firm in Boston and Larissa is a landscape architect.  We have both spent a lot of time traveling and met while working in San Francisco (one of our favorite places). We have have two young daughters and split or time between our time between Cambridge, MA and Ogunquit, ME when we are not traveling. Larissa is European so we frequently Travel to Europe to see friends and family in Germany, Turkey, Italy and France. Jordan's work also often brings him to Asia and the west coast.

We enjoy the outdoors as much as possible both beach and mountains. We are also pretty active we enjoy everything from Yoga to Biking to Surfing.  We are also into food and enjoy cooking and BBQing whenever we have time. 

We have been using AirBNB for over 3 yrs now. We have a good amount of experience hosting and really do enjoy meeting so many interesting people. As a host we are pretty hands off but there is we are needed. As long as our rules are observed it will be easy sailing for all. Looking forward having you as a guest.

host_about:
Harvard affiliate, design enthusiast, love to host and toast. The rest is history. Beyond all of the above, there is only one reason doing what we do- We are people's people :-). 

★★★★★★★★

FOR NEW airbnb user, below are some of the FAQ links for your perusal (questions & answers useful for new user). Please do let me know if you have any problem, my response would be faster than airbnb support team as sometimes their hotline as very busy (but I only can help you on general question).

GENERAL FAQ for guests before booking
www.airbnb.com/help/topic/traveling

FAQ: What are Airbnb Service Fees?
www.airbnb.com/help/question/104

FAQ: For How to Book
www.airbnb.com/help/question/85

FAQ: For How to make a payment / reservation
Please message me first before you book with the number of guests including kids. Tax of 13% is added on to the total and sent. 

FAQ: For How to Contact Airbnb Support
www.airbnb.com/help/question/9

FAQ: How and when do I make a payment for my reservation?
www.airbnb.com/help/question/92

FAQ: How can I view or print a billing receipt or itinerary for my trip?
www.airbnb.com/help/question/100

FAQ: How are cleaning fees added?
www.airbnb.com/help/question/58

FAQ: How does the Airbnb payment system work?
www.airbnb.com/help/question/51

Contact Number and Email Information will only be released until a booking is made.

Below is the FAQ on airbnb “Why can’t I call or email a host before booking?”: www.airbnb.com/help/question/111

We strongly recommend reviewing all cancellation policies before making your reservations: www.airbnb.com/home/cancellation_policies

Hope this helps you get to know how airbnb works :-)

For Pricing, at the listing page, enter check in date, check out date and total number of guests. The system will auto generate the price for your consideration. Regarding the currency display, it depends on your own setting, you can change your currency setting at the lower left panel of your airbnb page under the "LANGUAGE", you will see "CURRENCY" setting. Just click on it to change to any currency that you wish to display.

- Return Customer or Host or Guest with positive reviews with whatever possible discount on top of their daily / weekly / month rate OR VIP customer that keep booking over certain accumulated nights that I will offer extra discount OR Customer who had referred me many booking :-)

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Central Square, Cambridge, which is centered on the junction of Massachusetts Avenue, Prospect Street and Western Avenue. The diverse area is well known for its wide variety of ethnic restaurants, bars, live music and theatre venues. Many startups have moved research and office operations into the Square to take advantage of the relatively low costs and the proximity to MIT. Nearly demolished in the 1950’s, the neighborhood was spared and went so far as to experience a sort of renaissance. In 2012, the state of Massachusetts designated Central Square as an official Cultural District.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Central Square, Cambridge, which is centered on the junction of Massachusetts Avenue, Prospect Street and Western Avenue. The diverse area is well known for its wide variety of ethnic restaurants, bars, live music and theatre venues. Many startups have moved research and office operations into the Square to take advantage of the relatively low costs and the proximity to MIT. Nearly demolished in the 1950’s, the neighborhood was spared and went so far as to experience a sort of renaissance. In 2012, the state of Massachusetts designated Central Square as an official Cultural District.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located at Harvard Square, a triangular plaza near the center of Cambridge, Massachusetts. 'The Square' (as it is sometimes referred to locally) is both a commercial and residential center. Bookstores, theatres and music venues line the streets and enhance the energetic atmosphere. The neighborhood's central location, close proximity to university campuses and many public transportation options make it a bustling hub for people of all ages. During the day, take a stroll and discover the area's tranquil scenery. At night, there are countless bar and entertainment options. On the T, Downtown is a 15 minute ride while Logan International Airport is 30 minutes away.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Cambridge, Massachusetts is a charming, diverse city adjacent to Boston with beautiful views of the Charles River. A college town home to Harvard University and MIT, Cambridge is on the cutting edge of education, research and development. Residents of Cambridge enjoy being in the Greater Boston area without the hustle and bustle of Boston proper, creating the perfect balance between urban living and a suburban feel. Students attending college and living in the area hail from all over the world, giving Cambridge a worldly, international flavor. Harvard Square boasts historic red brick walkways and tree-lined blocks full of restaurants, shops, museums, entertainment centers and bookstores. The nearby Central Square is teeming with eclectic restaurants, bars, live music venues and small theaters. . Cambridge is an easy commute from downtown Boston via the “T” and the bus. Kendall Square and Central Square are within walking distance of Boston, just over the Charles River.
host_about: Furnished Quarters has been helping people stay different for 25 years. Driven by a passion for providing reliable short-term housing solutions worldwide, we aim to empower our guests with a seamless experience. neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is in Cambridgeport, a charming neighborhood just west of MIT’s campus. It’s a historic area known for Victorian-era homes and tree-lined streets, where the bordering Charles River adds to the neighborhood’s natural allure. In fact, Magazine Beach offers a scenic riverside escape here, making it perfect for picnics or leisurely strolls. Foodies enjoy an eclectic restaurant scene, with plenty of global cuisin, bakeries, and cocktail bars. This neighborhood perfectly balances the comforts of residential living with the vibrancy of city life. It’s a highly desirable spot just north of Boston. For those taking transportation into or out of the neighborhood, the Kendall/MIT or Central stops on the T are a just a short walk away.

neighborhood_overview:
I've lived in Boston/Cambridge for over 10 years and I couldn't recommend this location more for those who seek convenience without breaking your wallet.

Porter Square, like all the other locations in Cambridge, offers high quality life, convenience to all the local cafes, eateries, supermarkets, and most importantly, safe neighborhood! (as a female, this is on my top priority list!)

If you are here for a semester exchange, research, or fellowships at MIT, Harvard or Lesley (even downtown at Suffolk or work trips), highly recommend this location for those who seek comfortable stay in a safe and vibrant neighborhood but with a bit tight budget.

name: Rental unit in Somerville · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 2 baths
host_about: I love traveling and enjoy being in the center of everything or getting off the beaten path! My ideal vacation  has some of both. My favorite thing to do when traveling is see the unique natural and/or historic sites. I love hiking/walking, swimming, boating, etc. and don't mind a little adventure to get to a good spot! I also love trying new foods and doing a little local shopping.  For me, traveling is one of the most energizing and worthwhile things I can do. I most often travel with my siblings (I have 5!) or with my boyfriend. Girls trips are always fun too. I do less travel for work, but when I do I like to at least sneak in some "local" fun - like checking out a site or going to a nice restaurant.

name: Boutique hotel in Cambridge · ★4.50 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview: The hotel resides on a quiet residential street in the Baldwin neighborhood of central Cambridge. In the summer of 2021, the Baldwin neighborhood was named after black educator, Maria Baldwin who worked hard to represent the importance of racial justice and opportunities for women of color within Cambridge and beyond. To each side of the Baldwin neighborhood, lies Harvard and Porter square with Massachusetts Avenue serving as a connecter of the two. Directly to the east, the neighborhood borders the nearby city of Somerville. Surrounded by top institutions, there’s no shortage of activities, bars, and restaurants to experience during your stay at Prentiss House.
host_about: Thatch is an ever-evolving hospitality management company that specializes in co-living, hotels and apartment-hotels for short and long stays. Founded in 2010, Thatch's goal is to make Boston more accessible by providing innovative housing and hotel concepts at prices and on terms that put the value in hospitality back where it belongs - with the guests. We do this by stripping out non-essential services and amenities - like daily room cleaning and on-site food and beverage - and by centralizing our staff. In exchange, Thatch guests are afforded privacy, independence and more room in their travel budgets. Simple. Flexible. Functional. That's Thatch.

There are a few restaurants literally across the street, a bank, high end grocery store Formaggio, and other cute shops.
About one-half mile west of Harvard Square and Fresh Pond is the Observatory Hill neighborhood. Its neighborhood retail and business center is found around the intersection of Concord and Huron Avenues. Further out Huron Avenue towards Fresh Pond is the set of businesses known as Huron Village. Both of these centers offer a variety of neighborhood restaurants, grocery stores, some small offices, and unique retail and specialty shops that serve the surrounding community.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Central Square, Cambridge, which is centered on the junction of Massachusetts Avenue, Prospect Street and Western Avenue. The diverse area is well known for its wide variety of ethnic restaurants, bars, live music and theatre venues. Many startups have moved research and office operations into the Square to take advantage of the relatively low costs and the proximity to MIT. Nearly demolished in the 1950’s, the neighborhood was spared and went so far as to experience a sort of renaissance. In 2012, the state of Massachusetts designated Central Square as an official Cultural District.

Somerville is considered to be a highly walkable and bike-able city. Somerville hosts 21 Bluebikes (originally Hubway) stations, one of which is located right in Porter Square (Elm St).

Porter Square is a neighborhood in Cambridge and Somerville, between Harvard and Davis Squares. The Porter Square station has both the MBTA Red Line and the Commuter Rail Fitchburg Line. A major part of the Lesley University campus is located within the Porter Square area. There are also many shops and restaurants. Within the Art Deco-style building located at 1815 Massachusetts Avenue, The "Shops at Porter" have a recent history of being a center for Boston's Japanese community and is home to many Japanese eateries. Nearby, on Mass Ave on the other side of porter square is Yume Wo Katare, a ramen noodle restaurant that shouldn't be missed!

neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood houses one of the best-known high-tech and innovation hubs of the United States and arguably has the highest concentration of PhD's in the world.

However, this neighborhood is probably the most "below the radar" for tourists, but what it lacks in glamour it more than makes up for it in total, earnest hidden-gem-ness. Cruise down its main aorta, Cambridge Street, for access to some of the best fish markets, Portuguese bakeries, and well-loved bars in town. Mall rats can get their fill between the Cambridgeside Galleria and the Twin City Plaza shopping center, but one would be remiss to pass up stylish treasures at the Cambridge Antique Market. The residential makeup is richly diverse,anchored with strong Irish and Portuguese communities. Local pride runs thick.

Being just a few T stops away from downtown, it is a prime location to live.  With MIT and Kendall Square bordering the neighborhood as well as the exciting new Northpoint area, it represents the best of Boston and Cambridge. Be it through the local art scene, university presence, exciting employment centers, new high rises or access to the Charles River, this neighborhood has it all. This intellectual hotspot is also known for promoting ‘green living’ and this is one of the reasons why Charles River is one of America's cleanest urban rivers.

name: Rental unit in Cambridge · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Central Square, Cambridge, which is centered on the junction of Massachusetts Avenue, Prospect Street and Western Avenue. The diverse area is well known for its wide variety of ethnic restaurants, bars, live music and theatre venues. Many startups have moved research and office operations into the Square to take advantage of the relatively low costs and the proximity to MIT. Nearly demolished in the 1950’s, the neighborhood was spared and went so far as to experience a sort of renaissance. In 2012, the state of Massachusetts designated Central Square as an official Cultural District.

host_about:
As far as how I spend my day, if I'm not working, I like to walk around and explore new areas, travel or go to the beach. Before I left Charleston, I started taking surf lessens so that I would have something to do at the beach if I went by myself. At night, I like to go out with my friends or dance. I started taking ballroom dance my senior year of college and continued once I returned from overseas.  I recently picked up sailing again; I first sailed when I was young as a boy scout.

I'm ridiculously goal oriented.  Idle hands are the devils workshop... So I have plans on getting my first masters from ODU in Engineering Management, a easy to get masters due to my job.  Second maybe a pol-mil masters from either Stanford, Harvard or Yale.  Not sure what in yet, we'll see about that later.  And eventually either an EMBA or MBA in international economics.  My high school history teacher that I see every year asked me if i thought about a PhD.  I think I would rather have several masters and be more "well rounded"   

I also decided that I need a new hobby.  Since i just closed on my first house and was intrigued with the process as well as being able to look at all kinds of different places, I've decided I'm going to get my real estate brokers license.
